Log in to your Sumo Logic account.
Go to the Search section or tab.
Click on the "Metrics" tab within the search interface.
In the Metrics Explorer sidebar, select the appropriate metric data source that provides CPU usage metrics, such as "Prometheus" or "AWS CloudWatch."
From the available metrics in the sidebar, select the CPU usage metric that corresponds to your system or application. For example, you might choose cpu_usage or cpu_utilization.
Configure the time range for your exploration using the time picker at the top right corner. Let's select the last 24 hours.
The Metrics Explorer will generate a default visualization, such as a line chart, showing the CPU usage over the specified time range.
Explore the visualization by interacting with it. You can zoom in or out on specific time periods by clicking and dragging on the chart, or using the zoom buttons provided.
Customize the visualization by adjusting the time granularity, changing the chart type, or applying additional functions or filters using the options available in the sidebar.
Hover over the chart to view specific data points or values at different timestamps. You may see the CPU usage percentage at different time intervals.
If needed, you can add additional metrics or dimensions to the visualization, such as different CPU cores or specific hosts or instances.
Use the Metrics Explorer to gain insights from the CPU usage data by analyzing trends, identifying peak usage periods, or identifying any anomalies or abnormalities.
Save or export the metric exploration results if you want to revisit or share the analysis with others.
The specific CPU usage metric and options available in the Metrics Explorer may vary depending on your configured data sources and the metrics collected in your environment. Adjust the example above based on the actual CPU usage metric name and any specific dimensions or tags associated with it.






